io.requery

Interface EntityStore<T,R>

  • Type Parameters:
    T - the base class or interface to restrict all entities that are stored to (e.g. Persistable or Object or Serializable for instance. The purpose is to aid in the prevention of runtime errors by restricting the types at compile time.
    R - the operation return type. For an asynchronous implementation may return a Future or other type of promise representing the result of the operation.
    All Superinterfaces:
    AutoCloseable, Queryable<T>
    All Known Subinterfaces:
    BlockingEntityStore<T>, CompletionStageEntityStore<T>, SingleEntityStore<T>
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    CompletableEntityStore, EntityDataStore

    public interface EntityStore<T,R>
extends Queryable<T>, AutoCloseable
    The primary interface for interacting with Entity objects. This interface supports the basic insert/update/delete operations.

      • findByKey

        <E extends T,K> R findByKey(Class<E> type,
                            K key)
        Find an entity by the given key. This differs from selecting the key using a query in that the EntityCache if available may be checked first for the object. If an entity is found in the cache it will be returned and potentially no query will be made.
        Type Parameters:
        E - entity type
        K - key type
        Parameters:
        type - non null entity class type
        key - non null key value
        Returns:
        an operation returning the entity if found.

      • toBlocking

        BlockingEntityStore<T> toBlocking()
        Returns:
        a BlockingEntityStore version of this entity store. If the implementation is already blocking may return itself.
